    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-01-01T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-01-01T12:00:00-05:00" n="82"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d82">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89France/50: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-01-01T17:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 1, 1925—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. My 614, December 30, 7 p.m. I have requested both Herriot and Clémentel to say
                    nothing about the latter’s note, and believe it may be advisable, considering
                    nature of proposal, for Department to regard it as confidential.</p>
                <p>Detailed newspaper rumor has already appeared in regard to the note, but I
                    believe that this is attributable to source which has since been stopped. I am
                    informing press correspondents that there is no new development.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
